The paper discusses a new cognitive radio standard (IEEE 802.22) and proposes a distributed spectrum sensing technique for wireless regional area networks (WRANs). This involves the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the performance of spectrum sensing fusion mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
